# Specialized Modules - HTTP Response & Content Analysis

Complete toolkit for analyzing what URLs **return**, not just their structure.

## 📦 **Module Overview**

| Module | Purpose | Key Features |
|--------|---------|--------------|
| `http_inspector` | HTTP response analysis | Status codes, headers, timing, redirects |
| `security_analyzer` | Security headers & policies | CORS, CSP, HSTS, robots.txt |
| `redirect_mapper` | Redirect chain tracking | 301, 302, 307, meta-refresh, JS redirects |
| `content_inspector` | Content type analysis | MIME types, compression, encoding |
| `metadata_extractor` | HTML metadata extraction | Title, OpenGraph, Twitter Card, canonical |
| `cache_analyzer` | Cache behavior | Cache-Control, ETags, fingerprinting |
| `link_checker` | Link validation | Batch checking, retries, status reporting |
| `dom_parser` | HTML parsing | Element extraction, links, images, text |

---

## 🔍 **1. HTTP Inspector**

Comprehensive HTTP response analysis with status codes, headers, and timing.

```python
from unified_url_toolkit.specialized import inspect_url, get_status_info

# Inspect HTTP response
response = inspect_url('https://example.com')
print(f"Status: {response.status_code} - {response.reason}")
print(f"Server: {response.server}")
print(f"Response time: {response.response_time_ms}ms")

# Get status code details
status_info = get_status_info(404)
print(f"Category: {status_info.category}")
print(f"Is Error: {status_info.is_error}")
```markdown

**Features:**
- HEAD and GET requests
- Response timing analysis
- Server identification
- Header extraction
- Redirect detection
- Compression analysis


---

## 🔒 **2. Security Analyzer**

Analyze security headers, CORS policies, and robots.txt.

```python
from unified_url_toolkit.specialized import (
    analyze_security_headers,
    analyze_cors,
    fetch_robots_txt,
)

# Security headers analysis
security = analyze_security_headers(url, response.headers)
print(f"Security Score: {security.security_score}/100")
print(f"HSTS Enabled: {security.has_hsts}")
for issue in security.security_issues:
    print(f"Issue: {issue}")

# CORS analysis
cors = analyze_cors(url, response.headers)
print(f"CORS Enabled: {cors.is_cors_enabled}")
print(f"Security Level: {cors.cors_security_level}")

# robots.txt analysis
robots = fetch_robots_txt('https://example.com')
if robots.exists:
    print(f"Sitemaps: {robots.sitemaps}")
    print(f"Disallowed: {robots.disallowed_paths}")
```markdown

**Features:**
- HSTS, CSP, X-Frame-Options analysis
- CORS policy validation
- robots.txt parsing
- Meta robots tag analysis
- Security scoring
- Recommendations


---

## ↪️ **3. Redirect Mapper**

Track and analyze redirect chains including meta-refresh and JavaScript.

```python
from unified_url_toolkit.specialized import follow_redirect_chain

# Follow redirect chain
chain = follow_redirect_chain('http://example.com')
print(f"Total Redirects: {chain.total_redirects}")
print(f"Final URL: {chain.final_url}")
print(f"Permanent: {chain.permanent_redirects}")
print(f"Temporary: {chain.temporary_redirects}")

# Redirect details
for hop in chain.hops:
    print(f"{hop.url} -> {hop.redirect_type}")
```markdown

**Features:**
- HTTP redirects (301, 302, 307, 308)
- Meta refresh detection
- JavaScript redirect detection
- Redirect loop detection
- Cross-domain tracking
- Protocol upgrade tracking


---

## 📄 **4. Content Inspector**

Analyze MIME types, compression, and content characteristics.

```python
from unified_url_toolkit.specialized import (
    analyze_content,
    sniff_content_type,
)

# Analyze content
content = analyze_content(
    content_type="text/html; charset=utf-8",
    content_length="15234",
    content_encoding="gzip"
)

print(f"MIME: {content.mime_type}")
print(f"Category: {content.mime_category}")
print(f"Size: {content.content_length_human}")
print(f"Compressed: {content.is_compressed} ({content.compression_type})")
print(f"Is HTML: {content.is_html}")
```sql

**Features:**
- MIME type detection
- Content categorization
- Compression analysis (gzip, brotli, deflate)
- Binary vs text detection
- Content sniffing from bytes
- Size formatting


---

## 🏷️ **5. Metadata Extractor**

Extract HTML metadata, OpenGraph, Twitter Card, and canonical URLs.

```python
from unified_url_toolkit.specialized import extract_metadata

# Extract metadata
metadata = extract_metadata('https://example.com')

print(f"Title: {metadata.title}")
print(f"Description: {metadata.description}")
print(f"Canonical: {metadata.canonical_url}")

# OpenGraph
if metadata.has_opengraph:
    print(f"OG Title: {metadata.og_title}")
    print(f"OG Image: {metadata.og_image}")

# Twitter Card
if metadata.has_twitter_card:
    print(f"Twitter Card: {metadata.twitter_card}")
    print(f"Twitter Image: {metadata.twitter_image}")

# SEO
print(f"Indexable: {metadata.is_indexable}")
print(f"Robots: {metadata.robots_directives}")
```markdown

**Features:**
- HTML title, description, keywords
- OpenGraph tags
- Twitter Card tags
- Canonical URL
- Meta robots tags
- Favicon extraction
- Language detection


---

## 💾 **6. Cache Analyzer**

Analyze cache headers, fingerprinting, and optimization opportunities.

```python
from unified_url_toolkit.specialized import (
    analyze_cache,
    detect_fingerprint,
)

# Detect fingerprinting
has_fp, fp_type, fp_value = detect_fingerprint(
    "https://example.com/app.js?v=1.2.3"
)
print(f"Fingerprinted: {has_fp} ({fp_type}: {fp_value})")

# Analyze cache
cache = analyze_cache(
    url="https://example.com/app.js?v=1.2.3",
    cache_control="public, max-age=31536000, immutable",
    etag='"abc123"'
)

print(f"Cache Score: {cache.cache_score}/100")
print(f"Cacheable: {cache.is_cacheable}")
print(f"Max Age: {cache.max_age}s")
print(f"Immutable: {cache.immutable}")

for rec in cache.recommendations:
    print(f"Tip: {rec}")
```markdown

**Features:**
- Resource fingerprinting detection
- Cache-Control parsing
- ETag validation
- Freshness calculation
- Cache scoring (0-100)
- Optimization recommendations


---

## ✅ **7. Link Checker**

Comprehensive link validation with retries and batch processing.

```python
from unified_url_toolkit.specialized import (
    check_link,
    check_multiple_links,
)

# Check single link
result = check_link('https://example.com')
print(f"Status: {result.status.value}")
print(f"Alive: {result.is_alive}")
print(f"Response Time: {result.response_time_ms}ms")

# Batch checking
urls = ['https://example.com', 'https://test.org', 'http://broken.link']
report = check_multiple_links(urls, max_workers=10)

print(f"Success Rate: {report.success_rate:.1f}%")
print(f"Alive: {report.alive_links}")
print(f"Broken: {len(report.broken_links)}")
```markdown

**Features:**
- HEAD/GET requests
- Automatic retries
- Timeout handling
- Parallel batch processing
- Progress tracking
- Detailed reporting
- Slow link detection


---

## 🌳 **8. DOM Parser**

Advanced HTML parsing and element extraction.

```python
from unified_url_toolkit.specialized import (
    parse_html,
    extract_links,
    extract_images,
    extract_text,
)

# Parse HTML
soup = parse_html(html_content)

# Extract links
links = extract_links(soup, base_url='https://example.com')
for link in links:
    print(f"{link.text}: {link.url}")
    if link.is_external:
        print("  (external)")

# Extract images
images = extract_images(soup)
for img in images:
    print(f"{img.alt}: {img.src}")

# Extract text
text = extract_text(soup, strip=True)
```markdown

**Features:**
- BeautifulSoup integration
- Link extraction with context
- Image extraction
- Text extraction
- Attribute extraction
- CSS selector support
- DOM tree analysis


---

## 📊 **Complete Example**

```python
from unified_url_toolkit.specialized import *

url = "https://github.com"

# 1. HTTP Inspection
print("=== HTTP Analysis ===")
response = inspect_url(url)
print(f"Status: {response.status_code} ({response.response_time_ms:.0f}ms)")

# 2. Security
print("\n=== Security ===")
security = analyze_security_headers(url, response.headers)
print(f"Security Score: {security.security_score}/100")

# 3. Redirects
print("\n=== Redirects ===")
chain = follow_redirect_chain(url)
print(f"Redirects: {chain.total_redirects}")

# 4. Content
print("\n=== Content ===")
content = analyze_content(
    content_type=response.content_type,
    content_encoding=response.compression_type
)
print(f"Type: {content.mime_type}")
print(f"Compressed: {content.is_compressed}")

# 5. Metadata
print("\n=== Metadata ===")
metadata = extract_metadata(url)
print(f"Title: {metadata.title}")
print(f"OpenGraph: {metadata.has_opengraph}")

# 6. Cache
print("\n=== Cache ===")
cache_headers = get_cache_headers(response)
cache = analyze_cache(url, **cache_headers)
print(f"Cache Score: {cache.cache_score}/100")

print("\n✅ Complete analysis done!")
```markdown

---

## 🎯 **Use Cases**

### SEO Audit
```python
metadata = extract_metadata(url)
security = analyze_security_headers(url, headers)
cache = analyze_cache(url, **headers)

# Check meta tags
assert metadata.title is not None
assert metadata.description is not None
assert metadata.canonical_url is not None

# Check security
assert security.security_score > 70

# Check caching
assert cache.has_fingerprint
```markdown

### Link Validation
```python
report = check_multiple_links(urls, max_workers=20)

# Get broken links
for broken in report.broken_links:
    print(f"Fix: {broken}")

# Get slow links
for slow in report.slow_links:
    print(f"Optimize: {slow}")
```markdown

### Content Analysis
```python
soup = parse_html(html)
links = extract_links(soup)
images = extract_images(soup)

# External links
external = [l for l in links if l.is_external]
print(f"External links: {len(external)}")

# Missing alt tags
no_alt = [img for img in images if not img.alt]
print(f"Images without alt: {len(no_alt)}")
```markdown

